          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider" />

          <!-- Shape Section -->
          <div class="doc-section">
            <h3 id="shape" class="doc-h3">Shape</h3>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Icon buttons support two shape variants that control the border-radius of the container.</p>
            <div style="display: flex; gap: 24px; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-bottom: 24px;">
              <div style="flex: 1; min-width: 200px; padding: 24px; background: var(--prism-surface); border: 1px solid var(--prism-border); border-radius: 12px; text-align: center;">
                <div style="width: 48px; height: 48px; border: 2px dashed #006AFF; border-radius: 4px; margin: 0 auto 16px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; background: rgba(0, 106, 255, 0.05); color: #006AFF; font-weight: 600;">4px</div>
                <div style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--prism-text);">Square</div>
                <div style="font-size: 12px; color: var(--prism-text-muted); margin-top: 4px;">border-radius: 4px</div>
              </div>
              <div style="flex: 1; min-width: 200px; padding: 24px; background: var(--prism-surface); border: 1px solid var(--prism-border); border-radius: 12px; text-align: center;">
                <div style="width: 48px; height: 48px; border: 2px dashed #006AFF; border-radius: 50%; margin: 0 auto 16px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; background: rgba(0, 106, 255, 0.05); color: #006AFF; font-weight: 600;">50%</div>
                <div style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--prism-text);">Circle</div>
                <div style="font-size: 12px; color: var(--prism-text-muted); margin-top: 4px;">border-radius: 50%</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- ═══ USAGE TAB ═══ -->
        <div class="tab-content" id="tab-usage" style="display: none; padding-top: 32px;">

          <!-- When and Where to Use -->
          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="when-to-use" class="doc-section-title">When and Where to Use</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">An icon button triggers an action using a single icon without a text label, ideal for space-constrained interfaces.</p>

            <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 24px; margin-top: 24px;">
              <div style="padding: 24px; background: var(--prism-surface); border: 1px solid var(--prism-border); border-radius: 12px; transition: all 0.25s ease;">
                <h3 id="when-to-use-details" style="font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--prism-text); margin-bottom: 16px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px;">
                  <svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="#2563eb" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
                  When to use
                </h3>
                <ul class="doc-list" style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px; font-size: 14.5px;">
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 8px;">Toolbar actions where space is limited and icons are universally understood (edit, delete, close).</li>
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 8px;">Inline controls alongside other elements (close button on a tag or card).</li>
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 8px;">Toggle or secondary actions that don't require a text label.</li>
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 8px;">Repeated actions in data tables or list rows (row-level edit, delete).</li>
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent;">Floating action triggers (plus button to add an item).</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div style="padding: 24px; background: var(--prism-surface); border: 1px solid var(--prism-border); border-radius: 12px; transition: all 0.25s ease;">
                <h3 id="when-not-to-use" style="font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--prism-text); margin-bottom: 16px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px;">
                  <svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="#e42527" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12"/></svg>
                  When NOT to use
                </h3>
                <ul class="doc-list" style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px; font-size: 14.5px;">
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 8px;">For ambiguous or uncommon actions without a tooltip.</li>
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent;">When the action needs a text label for clarity -- use a Button instead.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider" />

          <!-- Type Selection Guide -->
          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="type-selection-guide" class="doc-section-title">Type Selection Guide</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Choose the right type based on the action's emphasis and context.</p>
            <table class="size-table" style="margin-top: 24px;">
              <thead><tr><th>Type</th><th>Use for</th><th>Example</th></tr></thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr><td><strong>Primary</strong></td><td style="color: var(--prism-text-muted);">High-emphasis primary actions</td><td style="color: var(--prism-text-muted);">FAB add button, main CTA icon</td></tr>
                <tr><td><strong>Secondary</strong></td><td style="color: var(--prism-text-muted);">Medium-emphasis supportive actions</td><td style="color: var(--prism-text-muted);">Edit action in a card header</td></tr>
                <tr><td><strong>Tertiary</strong></td><td style="color: var(--prism-text-muted);">Low-emphasis actions discoverable on hover</td><td style="color: var(--prism-text-muted);">Toolbar icons in a rich text editor</td></tr>
                <tr><td><strong>Outline</strong></td><td style="color: var(--prism-text-muted);">Actions that need a clear clickable boundary</td><td style="color: var(--prism-text-muted);">Filter toggle, sort controls</td></tr>
                <tr><td><strong>Danger</strong></td><td style="color: var(--prism-text-muted);">Destructive actions</td><td style="color: var(--prism-text-muted);">Delete row, remove item</td></tr>
                <tr><td><strong>Tertiary Grey</strong></td><td style="color: var(--prism-text-muted);">Lowest-emphasis neutral actions</td><td style="color: var(--prism-text-muted);">Close dialog, dismiss notification</td></tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider" />

          <!-- Best Practices -->
          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="detailed-guidelines" class="doc-section-title">Best Practices</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Visual and interaction guidelines to ensure icon buttons are effective, scalable, and accessible.</p>
            <div class="do-dont-grid">
              <div class="do-card"><span class="card-label">Do</span>
                <ul class="doc-list" style="border: none; background: transparent; padding: 0;">
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Always provide an aria-label</strong> that describes the action, not the icon (e.g., "Delete item" not "Trash icon").</li>
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Use universally recognized icons</strong> (close, add, edit, delete) to ensure immediate comprehension.</li>
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Use tooltips</strong> to show the action label on hover for sighted users.</li>
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Match icon button type</strong> to the Button type used nearby for visual consistency.</li>
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Use circle shape</strong> for FAB-style (floating action button) actions.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div class="dont-card"><span class="card-label">Don't</span>
                <ul class="doc-list" style="border: none; background: transparent; padding: 0;">
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Don't use for ambiguous actions</strong> without a tooltip to clarify the intent.</li>
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Don't use when action needs text</strong> -- use a full Button component instead.</li>
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Don't mix shapes</strong> in the same toolbar (square and circle).</li>
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Don't use danger type</strong> for non-destructive actions.</li>
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Don't disable without reason</strong> -- provide explanation via tooltip.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider" />

          <!-- Related -->
          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="related" class="doc-section-title">Related</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Components that complement or can be used alongside the Icon Button.</p>
            <div class="related-grid">
              <a href="Button.html" class="related-chip"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><rect x="3" y="5" width="18" height="14" rx="3"/></svg> Button</a>
              <a href="Tooltip.html" class="related-chip"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M21 15a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H7l-4 4V5a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h14a2 2 0 0 1 2 2z"/></svg> Tooltip</a>
              <a href="Badges.html" class="related-chip"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M12 8v4m0 4h.01"/></svg> Badge</a>
              <a href="Dropdown.html" class="related-chip"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><rect x="3" y="5" width="18" height="14" rx="2"/><polyline points="8 10 12 14 16 10"/></svg> Action Dropdown</a>
            </div>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider" />

          <!-- References -->
          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="references" class="doc-section-title">References</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Design tokens and resources for implementing the Icon Button component.</p>
            <ul class="doc-list">
              <li><strong>Figma Node:</strong> <code style="font-family: monospace; font-size: 13px; padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 6px; background: rgba(37,99,235,0.06); color: var(--prism-violet);">16456:29077</code> -- Component Set: Icon Button</li>
              <li><strong>Total Variants:</strong> 2 (Shape) x 6 (Type) x 4 (Size) x 5 (State) = <strong>240 variants</strong></li>
            </ul>
